summary:
Greetings! You have landed on a concise summary of my profile.

Originally from Warsaw, Poland, I am now an international student, allowing me to go wherever my journey takes me. I have had the privilege of living in Tilburg, Netherlands and Madrid, Spain, where I completed my BBA exchange semester at IE University.

Over the years, I have gained professional experience in a variety of business industries and positions, including consulting and analyst work, tutoring and creating/leading a student association. My extensive mathematical background and analytical skills allow me to generate value in my work. I am fluent in two languages (PL/ENG) and currently working on extending my skills to Dutch (A2).

In my free time, I enjoy staying active and participating in various sports activities. I currently represent Gepidae as a competitive volleyball player and have a passion for bodybuilding and nutrition. I also have a keen interest in acquiring new skills and knowledge, particularly in the tech sector.

When working in a team, I am comfortable taking a leadership role and am dedicated to fostering a positive team atmosphere.

If you think that my skills and personality could be an asset to your network, please do not hesitate to reach out and connect with me!
